rComments: Prof. Cooper is great! She gives the most clear instructions ever so just follow them and you'll do well. The readings she assigns are not necessary because her slides are SUPER detailed. Make sure to focus on the object list and you should be good to go for her midterm and final.
Dr. Cooper's lectures were very clear and concise, however the course covers a lot of history and it seemed almost too much to do in only one semester.  Exams were a bit difficult.

Great lecturer, she is very approachable. Her explanations are clear and concise. There are time when her lectures are boring. This is not because her explanations are bad or anything, its just that the content is boring. She is very understanding and lenient. If your having problems that involve the course, she can help you  with them.

Kate Coopers lectures are clear, concise. She gives specific examples that are thus required to answer midterm and final. Exams combination of essay and short question. Readings are mandatory in order to pass, must read in order to see whats going on.  Content was very boring. There are also quizzes that are given every other work worth 10%

Prof. Cooper is always available for help, tries to make lectures interesting, and respects her students. She's so nice that it made me regret skipping a few lectures. However, you don't HAVE to attend. The slides online are more than enough if you actually study from it. Textbook isn't necessary - save yourself $100. Would take her classes again.

She is SUPER clear, nice, and very helpful, though the course was a bit monotonous with a lot of content to memorize. The prof gives very clear directions for assignments, is fair, and gives the opportunity to get easy marks. She updates Blackboard often to keep you up to date, and really goes above and beyond to make sure you excel in the class.
